File: Traffic lights out of order in Cape Town, 21 January 2008, because of power cuts, or "load-shedding", as it is called, by the national electicity supplier, ESKOM. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom will implement Stage 2 load-shedding on Thursday. The power utility said load-shedding will start from 4pm until 11pm. LOAD-SHEDDING: Schedules, info, and how it affects you Eskom said this was due to a shortage of capacity. On Sunday, Eskom warned that unplanned breakdowns could result in load-shedding at short notice.